summary: But what if all cats were flerken, and they’re really sparse across the galaxies outside of earth, which has...600 million cats...
body: But what if all cats were flerken, and they’re really sparse across the galaxies outside of earth, which has…600 million cats according to google. And the rest of the galaxy can’t believe we cohabitate with this massively dangerous species and sometimes even have multiple living with us at a time. And what do we do with these little monsters with pocket dimensions in their stomachs? We use them to keep tiny disease baring mammals out of our buildings. We’re more afraid of the pestilence wrought by these tiny mammals than the tentacle-faced eldritch beings.

summary: cpt marvel post i guess? not 100% spoiler-free!
body:
cpt marvel post i guess? not 100% spoiler-free!

just came home from the cinema and i have to admit i kinda liked the movie. it’s not my fav mcu movie tbh but it was great. carol and fury have great chemistry, the skull/kree thing caught me off-guard (i haven’t read the comics so please bear with me) and it fits in the story of the mcu. oh and the visuals were amazing!

idk i’m easy when it comes to marvel. i like the great visuals and big characters and the action. so.. yeah. 🤷🏻‍♀️

summary: A spoiler free Captain Marvel review
title: A spoiler free Captain Marvel review
body:
Saw the movie and….it’s bad. Thing is, I can’t tell if it’s so bad it’s good like in Suicide Squad or just frustratingly bad like in The Last Jedi. 

But the plot makes zero sense. The more I think about it, the more it unravels. The more I say, “Wait, hold on, that doesn’t work either.” And, yet, at the same time, I really enjoyed watching Jackson cooing at a cat. It was seriously cute and funny. Mendelsohn was just plain old fun as usual. I really, really liked the character, Maria. (I only wished the movie had more of her. I want to check out Lynch’s other works now.) 

So, I watched it. And now I am ready for Endgame. Bring it on.

summary: So, I just saw Captain Marvel
title: So, I just saw Captain Marvel
body:
I liked it. It has nice colors, good music from 90s and some improvements in classical ‘origins of hero’ story, so that’s also plus. 

I love the way they showed how some characters were like in the past, but I thought that Coulson will have bigger role. But there was cool cosmic ginger kitty, so I feel bought. I give it 9/10.

P.S. Am I the only one who started cry on the very beginning, when they showed ‘Thank You, Stan’?
